Dorsum — Dorsal body setae long, linear lanceolate, well surpassing in length distance between consecutive bases (length of holotype and variations of seven paratypes ): v 1 49 (44 – 49); sc 1 (79 – 84); sc 2 55 (50 – 55); c 1 70 (66 – 72); c 2 68 (68 – 72); c 3 60 (57 – 61); d 1 60 (60 – 63); d 2 73 (64 – 74);
e 1 52
(53 – 59); e 2 66 (64 – 72); f 1 47 (47 – 51); f 2 30 (28 – 39); h 1 26 (23 – 26). Dorsal striation with rounded lobes on propodosoma and hysterosoma up to third row of dorsal setae ( e ).

Legs — Length inferior to body length, leg I 165 (165 – 169) µm long (from trochanter to tarsus, 
holotype
and variations of seven 
paratypes
), leg II 148 (140 – 146), leg III 150 (142 – 154), leg IV 170 (169 – 175). Length of segments of leg I as follows (
Figs. 9A, B
): trochanter 18 (18 – 21), femur 50 (48 – 52), genu 22 (22 – 25), tibia 29 (30 – 31), tarsus 46 (42 – 45). Leg setal count as follows (
